        <hl1>A Poor Example</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>As a Mets fan, I find it quite interesting that Roger Clemens says that emotions got the best of him. What type of precedent is this setting for people watching at home? Any time we're in a pressure situation and we bubble over with emotion, we can act out as we please? Joe Torre said Clemens is an emotional pitcher (as if this is an excuse).</p>
        <p>ROBERT C. FITTON  Mineola, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
